  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (COMPOUND-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed. This package declares assuranceLevel Medium and an Accepted decision outcome; however, multiple credibility factors show achievedLevel strictly below requiredLevel, including at least one factor where the gap is critical. The declared assurance level is inconsistent with the structural evidence and triggers COMPOUND-03.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
