      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Pressure-flow characteristic validation across 5 operating points"
    }
  ],
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must be verified under a formal SQA plan with documented test suite covering hemolysis model routines; version control and audit trail required for MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "SQA documentation covers standard CFD routines but the hemolysis damage accumulation subroutine lacks an independent unit-test suite. Achieved Gradation 3 against a required Gradation 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal order-of-accuracy study (Richardson extrapolation or equivalent) must be completed for the hemolysis transport equation on geometries representative of the pump impeller passage.",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy verification was performed only on a simplified 2-D pipe flow benchmark. No verification study was conducted on the rotating impeller geometry relevant to the COU. This gap is critical for MRL 5 and directly undermines the declared Medium assurance level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be reported for hemolysis index QoI on at least three systematically refined meshes; GCI must be below 5% for MRL 5 acceptance.",
      "rationale": "Three-mesh GCI study completed; reported GCI of 8.2% on hemolysis index exceeds the 5% threshold. Mesh refinement beyond the coarsest level was limited by computational budget."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (hematocrit, temperature, anticoagulant protocol, blood source) must be documented and matched to simulation boundary conditions within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Hematocrit and temperature were matched; however, anticoagulant protocol differed between experimental runs and was not propagated as an uncertainty source in the Monte Carlo analysis."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E% or validation metric u_val) must be computed for hemolysis index at each of the 5 operating points with uncertainty intervals reported.",
      "rationale": "Comparison metrics were computed at 4 of 5 operating points; the highest-speed condition lacked experimental replication sufficient to compute a meaningful validation metric with uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The modeled QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) must be demonstrated to be the clinically relevant metric for VAD acceptance decisions.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the accepted regulatory QoI for hemolysis assessment. Mapping from simulation output to NIH is direct and well-documented. Requirement met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use a geometry and operating envelope sufficiently similar to the intended VAD COU; any geometric or operational differences must be quantified as extrapolation uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Validation used the FDA generic pump geometry which shares impeller topology with the target device. Rotational speed range partially overlaps the COU envelope; the highest-speed VAD operating point falls outside the validated range by 15%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence must be demonstrated to below 1e-5 residual for all transport equations including the hemolysis scalar; round-off error contribution must be estimated.",
      "rationale": "Iterative residuals for the hemolysis scalar equation were reported at 1e-3, two orders of magnitude above the required threshold. No round-off error analysis was performed. This represents a critical gap; the achievedLevel of 1 against a requiredLevel of 3 is the primary driver of COMPOUND-03 in this package."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
