      "acceptanceCriteria": "Evidence must be provided that the analyst team followed documented simulation protocols and that independent review of boundary condition setup was performed.",
      "rationale": "Simulation protocols were documented; however, independent review of boundary condition setup was performed by a team member rather than an independent reviewer, which does not satisfy the MRL 5 independence requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The power-law hemolysis damage model must be compared against at least one alternative constitutive model; model-form uncertainty must be propagated through the Monte Carlo UQ.",
      "rationale": "Model form assessment was scoped out due to resource constraints. No alternative hemolysis model comparison was performed and model-form uncertainty was not included in the Monte Carlo analysis. Factor flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All uncertain model inputs (viscosity, density, power-law exponents, inlet velocity profile) must be characterised with probability distributions and propagated through Monte Carlo UQ.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed on geometric and flow boundary condition inputs. Power-law hemolysis model constants (C, alpha, beta) were treated as fixed nominal values rather than uncertain parameters, omitting a significant source of input uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
